  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_155038574" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/155038574" />
    <a title="Mike (the Paladin)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2187043-mike-the-paladin"><img alt="Mike (the Paladin)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1528431476p2/2187043.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/155038574?book_show_action=true">Mar 17, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mike (the Paladin)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mike (the Paladin)" href="/user/show/2187043-mike-the-paladin">Mike (the Paladin)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audio CD 9780743567077" href="/book/show/21388.The_Silence_of_the_Lambs">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer155038574" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4366085316129578943">A creep fest or gore fest that I read some time ago. I was into &quot;audio books&quot; in my work vehicle at the time, listening to books between jobs and on my commute rather than the radio....I listened to this book. Was I crazy or something?<br/><br/>I&apos;ve never read anything else by Harris. My wife was the &quot;horror&quot; fan (and no matter what genre this book gets placed in officially it really belongs with horror). She &quot;read, Red Dragon&quot; (read that out loud and it sounds a bit odd....&quot;read Red&quot;? Oh well just a whim</span>
  <span id="freeText4366085316129578943" style="display:none">A creep fest or gore fest that I read some time ago. I was into "audio books" in my work vehicle at the time, listening to books between jobs and on my commute rather than the radio....I listened to this book. Was I crazy or something?<br /><br />I've never read anything else by Harris. My wife was the "horror" fan (and no matter what genre this book gets placed in officially it really belongs with horror). She "read, Red Dragon" (read that out loud and it sounds a bit odd...."read Red"? Oh well just a whimsical mind at work here.) and as I recall wasn't that taken with it, but when the movie came out this one showed up everywhere. (The movie of Silence of the Lambs that is...there is also a movie of Red Dragon of course. LOL) I never went to the theater to see it, though I did subsequently see it on TV. (By the way I agree Hopkins did a good Lecter, and Foster did a good Clarice)<br /><br />This is one of the great angst novels of all time... Hannibal Lecter is a unique character when it comes to the "I kind of like the guy...but he might kill and eat me" character slot, he holds the trophy. B. Bill is also a nasty piece of work, but don't worry no ambivalence here. You probably won't like him, he's a bit...antisocial. (Yes I know he's had a horrible life, rough childhood, unloved, etc....and that's awful. I'm sure his "situation" is all society's fault, still not a great reason for bloody, brutal, murder. Really.)<br /><br />If this book doesn't keep you awake listening to those creaks the house makes or the noise coming from the next apartment... well, maybe we ought to worry about you????<br /><br />Can I call this a "good book"...well not the adjective I might have chosen, but it is exceptionally well written. Enjoy, if you can...though if you actually "enjoy" this book, like I said, maybe you're someone about whom we ought to be concerned...</span>
  <a data-text-id="4366085316129578943" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

