<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6675070134037423756"><i>Librarian Note:<br/>There is more than one author in the Goodreads database with this name.</i><br/><br/>Thomas Harris began his writing career covering crime in the United States and Mexico, and was a reporter and editor for the Associated Press in New York City. His first novel, <i>Black Sunday</i>, was printed in 1975, followed by <i>Red Dragon</i> in 1981, <i>The Silence of the Lambs</i> in 1988, <i>Hannibal</i> in 1999, and <i>Hannibal Risin</i></span>
  <span id="freeText6675070134037423756" style="display:none"><i>Librarian Note:<br />There is more than one author in the Goodreads database with this name.</i><br /><br />Thomas Harris began his writing career covering crime in the United States and Mexico, and was a reporter and editor for the Associated Press in New York City. His first novel, <i>Black Sunday</i>, was printed in 1975, followed by <i>Red Dragon</i> in 1981, <i>The Silence of the Lambs</i> in 1988, <i>Hannibal</i> in 1999, and <i>Hannibal Rising</i> in 2006.</span>
